<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="117" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,258,2011]" pageId="3" pageNumber="117">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1266,1291]" pageId="3" pageNumber="117">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific name refers to the native “ 
<taxonomicName box="[790,853,1266,1291]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Conognatha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="121" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="puris" status="sp. nov.">Puris</taxonomicName>
”, who lived in the Paraíba river area, near Serra da Mantiqueira, where is located the municipality of Itatiaia.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="119" pageId="3" pageNumber="117" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,258,2011]" pageId="3" pageNumber="117">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1338,1363]" pageId="3" pageNumber="117">Remarks.</emphasis>
Both the new species are similar to each other in general shape of the body, general pattern of setae, maculae and bands, form and pattern of interstriae. In contrast, they differ from each other by the colour and reflections on head, pronotum (
<figureCitation box="[515,595,1410,1435]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 7" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1962,1984]" captionTargetBox="[170,1422,276,1919]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[164,1423,267,1940]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 7. Conognatha (Pithiscus) coffeatus Portela &amp; Mermudes sp. nov., holotype male: 1 and 3, habitus; 2, lateral view; 4, frontal view of head; 5, ventral view of antennae; 6, shape of pronotum; 7, dorsal view of aedeagus. Scale bar: 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/224727/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="117">
Figs. 
<number box="[581,595,1411,1435]" pageId="3" pageNumber="117" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
and 
<figureCitation box="[656,671,1411,1435]" captionStart="FIGURES 8 – 14" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1786,1808]" captionTargetBox="[167,1430,207,1764]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[157,1430,193,1765]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 8 – 14. Conognatha (Pithiscus) puris Portela &amp; Mermudes sp. nov., holotype male: 8 and 10, habitus; 9, lateral view; 11, frontal view of head; 12, ventral view of antennae; 13, shape of pronotum; 14, dorsal view of aedeagus. Scale bar: 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/224728/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="117">
<number box="[656,671,1411,1435]" pageId="3" pageNumber="117" value="8.0">8</number>
</figureCitation>
), ventral surface and legs, by the presence of a short longitudinal groove between the vertex and the frons in 
<taxonomicName box="[639,777,1447,1470]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Conognatha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="puris" status="sp. nov." subGenus="Pithiscus">
<emphasis box="[639,777,1447,1470]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="117">C. (P.) puris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[784,874,1446,1471]" pageId="3" pageNumber="117" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[784,874,1446,1471]" pageId="3" pageNumber="117">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
(
<figureCitation box="[889,971,1446,1471]" captionStart="FIGURES 8 – 14" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1786,1808]" captionTargetBox="[167,1430,207,1764]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[157,1430,193,1765]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 8 – 14. Conognatha (Pithiscus) puris Portela &amp; Mermudes sp. nov., holotype male: 8 and 10, habitus; 9, lateral view; 11, frontal view of head; 12, ventral view of antennae; 13, shape of pronotum; 14, dorsal view of aedeagus. Scale bar: 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/224728/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="117">
Fig. 
<number box="[942,971,1447,1471]" pageId="3" pageNumber="117" value="11.0">11</number>
</figureCitation>
), shape of the frons rectangular in 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Conognatha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="coffeatus" status="sp. nov." subGenus="Pithiscus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="117">C. (P.) coffeatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[260,350,1482,1507]" pageId="3" pageNumber="117" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[260,350,1482,1507]" pageId="3" pageNumber="117">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
(
<figureCitation box="[366,435,1482,1507]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 7" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1962,1984]" captionTargetBox="[170,1422,276,1919]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[164,1423,267,1940]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 7. Conognatha (Pithiscus) coffeatus Portela &amp; Mermudes sp. nov., holotype male: 1 and 3, habitus; 2, lateral view; 4, frontal view of head; 5, ventral view of antennae; 6, shape of pronotum; 7, dorsal view of aedeagus. Scale bar: 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/224727/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="117">
Fig. 
<number box="[419,435,1483,1507]" pageId="3" pageNumber="117" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
), trapezoidal in 
<taxonomicName box="[618,756,1483,1506]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Conognatha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="puris" subGenus="Pithiscus">
<emphasis box="[618,756,1483,1506]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="117">C. (P.) puris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[772,852,1482,1507]" captionStart="FIGURES 8 – 14" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1786,1808]" captionTargetBox="[167,1430,207,1764]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[157,1430,193,1765]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 8 – 14. Conognatha (Pithiscus) puris Portela &amp; Mermudes sp. nov., holotype male: 8 and 10, habitus; 9, lateral view; 11, frontal view of head; 12, ventral view of antennae; 13, shape of pronotum; 14, dorsal view of aedeagus. Scale bar: 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/224728/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="117">
Fig. 
<number box="[825,852,1483,1507]" pageId="3" pageNumber="117" value="11.0">11</number>
</figureCitation>
) and of the antennae sensory fields (superficial and rounded in 
<taxonomicName box="[281,463,1519,1543]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Conognatha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="coffeatus" subGenus="Pithiscus">
<emphasis box="[281,463,1519,1543]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="117">C. (P.) coffeatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
